Original: There is an extravagantly bound book
on the shelf at the dead end. You
pluck it from the shelf and read...
[Page]
"Since we are so few, we'll need help
to execute our plan. We've begun to
create servitor races to help us.
[Page]
"Though they obviously need food as
well. If they needed the same food
we do, that would hardly be progress.
[Page]
"So we built them to resist the poison
found in the wilderness. The other
plan's research came in handy there.
[Page]
"That taken care of, we began to take
steps to proceed with our project..."
[Page]
The account ends there.

Original: There is an extravagantly bound book
on the shelf at the dead end. You
pluck it from the shelf and read...
[Page]
"Our first servants are highly skilled
combatants. They're used to protect us
as we explore and for physical labor.
[Page]
"Their strength comes from the mutated
bodies of wild animals. Each one has
a unique look from the animal used.
[Page]
"Our second servants are built for
intelligence, to support our research.
Their minds rival that of our own.
[Page]
"But their bodies are frail and can't
take extreme experimentation. I warned
the committee not to do it, but..."
[Page]
The account ends there.

Original: After navigating the hall of toxins
and shadow, you reach a corridor.
Thankfully, it is absent of traps.
[Page]
As you walk around the corridor, you
notice words written at your feet.
[Page]
The black ink has faded, making most
of it illegible, but this much at
least you can make out:
[Page]
"The devourer is sealed. Do not take
the insect lightly. Be very afraid of
what possesses it. DO NOT free it."
[Page]
Judging by the quickly scrawled note,
it seems the writer was in a rather
desperate hurry.
[Page]
You remember the skeleton's note on
B1F referencing an "insect" as well.
It could be important later...
[Page]
The exploration continues...

Original: When you open your eyes, you see a

[Page]

work, but it seems some mechanism has
transported you here.
[Page]

you will have to be even more careful
with the map you draw.

Original: As you progress through the dreadful
maze, you find a large shelf situated
at a dead end. There is a note here...
[Page]
[Color:5]"DANGER! Specimens intended for
disposal! DO NOT TOUCH!"[Color:0] Next to the
note is an array of specimen jars.
[Page]
You frown. The note is clear that the
specimens are not to be touched...
Will you handle them anyway?
